        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.constantsInComparison.comment=Always put constants on the left, as it simply eliminates any possibility of inadvertant assignment (\=) when you meant equality check (\=\=), because the compiler will not allow assignment to a constant. Get in the habit all the time (even for &lt; or &gt; ), and you never have to worry about it. --Rusty\r\n\r\nMoving this to high. --Rusty 07/12/26
