        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.analysis.audit.rule.effectivejava.favorStaticMemberClassesOverNonStatic.comment=Good idea, but there will for sure be needed exceptions, so we'll not litter every audit report with "violations" that are not. --Rusty
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.restrictedPackages.severity=1
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.obsoleteModifierUsage.autoResolutionEnabled=false
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.noDBDriverLoading.severity=0
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.hibernate.referencedClassNotDefined.comment=We currently do not use Hibernate. --Rusty 2007/05/09
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.restrictedSuperclasses.severity=2
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.spring.useTypeForConstructorArgumentMatching.enabled=true
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.analysis.mutableConstantField.comment=No, sometimes one needs to do this. --Rusty 01/03/06
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.defineConstantsInInterfaces.comment=Not always the best approach, so we'll not litter every instance of every audit reports with supposed "violations" of this rule that simply are not. --Rusty
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.inappropriateLanguageInJava.comment=New rule added to v4.6.0 build 2007.02.07. Well begin using it when the need comes up. --Rusty 2/13/07\r\n\r\nNo example of offending code?  --Jason 2/5/09
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.unusedMethod.comment=Clearly. --Rusty\r\n\r\nYes, it would be a nice rule, but it's flagging private constructors on inner classes as unused methods\! --Rusty (8/29/05)\r\n\r\nFiled a bug with CodePro.  Let's hope they fix it faster than Sun fixes their bugs\!  --Jason 2/5/2009
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.documentClosingBraces.comment=Please... I do this often for long methods and for loops, and at the end of every inner class, but I wouldn't force it on anyone--we force plenty of other "strange" rules on people--let's not push them to far\! \=\:-D --Rusty
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.toStringMethodUsage.comment=Turning all internationalization rules on. Some, if not many, of them will be unncessary on the server side code, and some, if not many, will impose unnecessary difficulty on server side programmers. However, this will be an internationalized application, and for each idiom prevented by these rules there is an alternative way to achieve the same effect. We can also ease up on some of them as experience permits. --Rusty\r\n\r\nThere is now a case where violating this audit rule is legitimate, so changing the  severity to medium.  --Jason 2/9/09
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.analysis.audit.rule.effectivejava.obeyEqualsContract.obeyGeneralContractOfEquals.comment=Yes. See Effective Java. --Rusty
