        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.spaceAroundOperators.comment=Yes, this\r\n\r\n((a+(b*c))/d) \r\n\r\nis simply too cramped without real justification, especially if one or more of the operands has a post or pre-fix decremnt/incrment attached to it\:\r\n\r\n((--a+(b++*++c))/d) \r\n\r\nWhat, exactly, is going on above? I don't know, let's let it breath a bit and see\:\r\n\r\n( ( --a + ( b++ * ++c ) ) / d )\r\n\r\nOh, thanks\! Now that's much easier to read\!  But oh my, a few extra spaces in an expression, will it kill you, especially with 100 charaters/line to work with? I hope not\! I hope you live\! (See rule "use a space after a comma" for more editorial on this same theme.)\r\n\r\n--Rusty
