        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.expressionValue.comment=Wrong\! This practice is good for implicitly communicating formulas. For example, which of the following communicates both your intentions and the fact that 's' is 10 minutes worth of millisecs without even having to say so\:\r\n\r\ns \= 1000 * 60 * 10;\r\n\r\nor\r\n\r\ns \= 600000;\r\n\r\nAnd when you need to change it to N minutes \!\= 10, you just change the 10; you don't recalcuate the whole expression.\r\n\r\n --Rusty
