        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.stringTokenizer.comment=Turning all internationalization rules on. Some, if not many, of them will be unncessary on the server side code, and some, if not many, will impose unnecessary difficulty on server side programmers. However, this will be an internationalized application, and for each idiom prevented by these rules there is an alternative way to achieve the same effect. We can also ease up on some of them as experience permits. --Rusty\r\n\r\nScott wants to use StringTokenizer, so we'll turn this rule off for now, at least until we find an I18N friendly approach to string tokenizing that everyone can use easily. --Rusty 01/03/06
