        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.localDeclaration.comment=Yes, good idea, but this rule's impl is just too narrowly defined. So except in loops, as long as you keep local variable declarations as narrowly scoped as possbile, declare locals where you see fit. The three most important things about local variables\:\r\n\r\n(1) Don't declare local variables in loops.\r\n(2) Declare locals that are set to value only once to be final (except when their use within a needed try/catch/finally construct prevents or makes it difficult). \r\n(3) Keep local variable scope as small as possible. \r\n\r\n--Rusty
