        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.avoidNestedAssignments.comment=Yes, despite what you want to believe, this practice does not make your code easier to read, nor does such "cleverness" make you seem smarter to other developers. --Rusty\r\n\r\nThis rule is currently flagging expressions like\r\n\r\n     foo[k++] \= getFoo();\r\n\r\nas nested assignemnts.\r\n\r\nTherefore, turning this rule off and sending a change request to Instantations asking them the either eliminate this as a violation or to add options to the param pane that allow you to optionally exclude it as a violation. Will turn it back on if they make the change for us. --Rusty 01/06/06\r\n\r\nInstantiations as not yet addressed the above.  Leaving this rule off.  --Jason 02/05/2009.
