        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.hidingInheritedStaticMethods.comment=Clearly an easily avioded practice that has no value, and only for sure leads to possible confusion. --Rusty\r\n\r\nNope, found a time and place for exempting classes from this rule. See http\://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/javax/swing/plaf/ComponentUI.html\#createUI(javax.swing.JComponent). So turning this rule off temporarily until CodePro updates it to allow exempting specific classes from enforcement. --Rusty 08/10/06\r\n\r\nCodePro introduced exemption of specific classes/metods, so turning this rule back on. --Rusty 2007/12/26\r\n\r\nNope, not fixed, the "exemptions" pane doesn't work. --Rusty 2007/12/26\r\n\r\nLooks like it's been fixed.  --Jason 2/4/2009.
