        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.variableShouldBeFinal.comment=Yep. For sure. Assists greatly in showing the intention of your algrothm, enables the compiler to catch some algorithm problems, enables some optimizations. --Rusty\r\n\r\nTurning this good rule off for now as it is being confused by the new 1.5 for loop syntax. Sent a bug report to Instantiations. Will turn it back on once it's fixed. --Rusty (8/29/50).\r\n\r\nCodePro says this is fixed, so turning it back on. --Rusty 01/03/06\r\n
