        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.checkEnabledBeforeDebug.comment=A large code base will have many thousands of log4j debug() calls embedded in it, and not having every debug() wrapped in an if-enabled check unnecessarily slows a production system down through the creation and garbage collection of countless totally useless String instances. I reduced the runtime on a multi-day batch system by 35% by simply wrapping every debug() in an if-enabled check. Since if its use were optional many people simply would not use it at all, its use will not be optional. --Rusty 
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.analysis.appletFieldSecurity.severity=2
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.analysis.preventOverwritingOfExternalizableObjects.readExternalPatterns=255
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.emptyFinalizeMethod.severity=2
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.analysis.unusedReturnValue.comment=Too restrictive. --Rusty 03/13/06
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.analysis.jUnitChecks.enabled=true
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.unnecessaryExceptions.severity=2
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.javaserverfaces.actionMethodReturnsUnknownValue.comment=Not currently doing JavaServer Faces development. --Rusty 2007/05/09
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.explicitThisUsage.explicitThisAbsent=true
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.javaserverfaces.noValidationMessage.comment=Not currently doing JavaServer Faces development. --Rusty 2007/05/09
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.efficientExpression.comment=In the internationalization rules they say not to use the parseXXX() methods, then in this rule it is used as an example of the prefered approach\! We just can't know how many of their "most efficient code possible" choices will cause us problems, thus we'll not use it. --Rusty
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.commandExecution.comment=Much to general. We could easily have cases where we need/want this, and we don't want those showing up forever in our audit reports as "violations". --Rusty
        com.instantiations.assist.eclipse.audit.largeNumberOfMethods.severity=0
